This evaluation is based on an extension of the R-matrix analysis  325 1451
to 8 MeV neutron energy, and the addition of the two-body channels 325 1451
n+6Li*(2.186), n+6Li**(3.563), and p+6He.  Experimental data for   325 1451
reactions involving those channels clarified the properties of two 325 1451
3/2- levels that show up as interference effects in the 4-6 MeV    325 1451
region.  The mf=3 cross sections were matched in the region 5-8    325 1451
MeV to experimental data and the previous evaluation at energies   325 1451
above 8 MeV.  The reason for the broad matching region is that     325 1451
the calculated (n,n')d alpha breakup cross section (mt=32) was     325 1451
under-predicted by the analysis due to the two-body assumption     325 1451
made for the d+5He and n+6Li* channels.  The data given for mt=32  325 1451
represent the sum of the (n,n')d alpha continuum cross section     325 1451
and the cross section for 6Li(n,n')6Li* (what would normally be    325 1451
mt=51 and was actually included in previous versions, going back   325 1451
to ENDF/B-VI [see below] as mt=53).  The inelastic cross section   325 1451
in mt=52, previously recorded in mt=57 in ENDF/B-VI and later) is  325 1451
for the second excited (T=1) state of 6Li, which decays only by    325 1451
gamma emission.                                                    325 1451
                                                                   325 1451
The total cross section in mt=1 was chosen to follow the precise   325 1451
data of Abfalterer et al. at energies above 5.3 MeV, and is there- 325 1451
fore somewhat lower than the previous evaluation in that region.   325 1451
Other data references will be given in a more detailed file-1      325 1451
description at a later date.                                       325 1451
                                                                   325 1451
The mt=32 energy-angle spectra in mf=6 for the (n,n'd)alpha re-    325 1451
action have been retained from the previous version, and may be    325 1451
updated at a later time.  The Legendre coefficients in mf=6 for    325 1451
elastic scattering (mt=2), inelastic scattering to the second      325 1451
level (mt=52), and for the (n,p) and (n,t) reactions (mt=103 and   325 1451
700) were extrapolated to energies above the range of the analysis 325 1451
to 20 MeV, and should be used with caution above 8 MeV.            325 1451
                                                                   325 1451
