                                                                   325 1451
Elastic scattering (n+6Li scattering) and 6Li(n,t)4He reaction     325 1451
were obtained at LANL by state of the art R-matrix analysis [1]    325 1451
of the 7-Li system. This system contains data for all possible     325 1451
reactions among t+4He and n+6Li at energies extending from the     325 1451
t+4He threshold (well below the n+6-Li threshold) up to energies   325 1451
corresponding to 4 MeV incident neutrons. Also included are        325 1451
n+6Li* channels to simulate the effects of n+d+ breakup. A very    325 1451
good fit is obtained to the more than 3300 data points, with a     325 1451
chi-square per degree of freedom of 1.164.                         325 1451
                                                                   325 1451
Of particular note is the excellent fit to the t+4He scattering    325 1451
data, which have very small uncertainties. This is true in         325 1451
particular at energies near the obvious resonance structure        325 1451
in the 6-Li(n,t) reaction. These high-precision charged-particle   325 1451
elastic scattering measurements put stringent constraints on       325 1451
fitting the neutron data through the unitarity of the              325 1451
scattering matrix.                                                 325 1451
                                                                   325 1451
References:                                                        325 1451
[1] G.M. Hale, "Covariances from light-element R-matrix            325 1451
analyzes", Nuclear Data Sheets, 109, 2812 (2008).                  325 1451
